docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:5:| A-070 | Until a persisted service-evidence shape proves dates, continuity, recipient entity, and evidence reference, `employment_or_service_years >= 3` alone must not satisfy BR-006; the active-member module returns `manual_evidence_required` for that route. | BR-006 names three continuous years to SFPCL/subsidiary/step-down entities, but the current profile stores only a numeric summary and the source schema does not define service-event rows. Treating the scalar as complete proof invents missing evidence. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` BR-006; `docs/source/data-model.md` §10.2/§11.5; `docs/source/codebase-design.md` §10.2; architecture review `2026-07-12_220748_architecture_review` | 006Z5-active-member-evidence-and-verification-governance-closure | High | No | 2026-07-12 | Resolved by 006Z5: `MemberServiceEvidence` persists the conservative dated recipient/evidence facts and the scalar remains summary-only. Missing qualifying evidence still returns `manual_evidence_required`. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:54:| A-049 | Until the source defines how selected `LandHolding.area_acres`, `CropPlan.planned_area_acres`, and nullable profile `land_area_under_cultivation_acres` are reconciled for BR-020, 006C2 will block calculation when the applicable verified acreage facts disagree; it will not invent a min/max/priority formula. | Functional BR-020 requires acreage under cultivation, while the API/data model expose three related acreage facts without a precedence or reconciliation rule. Current 006C sums selected owned acreage and can overstate the land limit when cultivation evidence is lower. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` BR-020/BR-022; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §23.1-§23.3; `docs/source/data-model.md` §10.2, §11.7-§11.8, §14.2, §35.1; architecture review `2026-07-10_092630_architecture_review` | 006C2-cultivated-acreage-source-hardening and future policy confirmation | High | Yes | 2026-07-10 | Safe interim behavior is a structured validation blocker with no assessment/audit/workflow mutation. If the client confirms an authoritative source or formula, replace the equality guard, version the rule, and preserve existing snapshots. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:57:| A-052 | Supersedes A-051's claim that assessment UUIDs alone preserve historical locality: explicit successful assessment reruns retain the UUID while replacing current facts, so 006E2 will keep the IDs only as provenance and persist immutable canonical projection copies on the appraisal. | Architecture review proved a same-UUID rerun can replace cultivated acreage, limits, policy, eligibility, and exception facts after appraisal creation. API design §3 requires decision snapshots; no FK to a mutable current assessment can provide that evidence. | `docs/adr/ADR-0003-freeze-appraisal-prerequisite-projections.md`; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §3/§23-§24; architecture review `2026-07-10_173305_architecture_review` | 006E2-appraisal-source-contract-and-snapshot-hardening and later review/sanction/reporting slices | High | Yes | 2026-07-10 | Implement the additive immutable snapshots and safe legacy provenance rules before 006F. Do not alter the already reviewed explicit assessment-rerun contract. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:58:| A-053 | M04-FR-001/M04-FR-002 appraisal task creation/role assignment remain intentionally deferred to the owner-planned generic task engine in 012EA; `prepared_by_user` is an action fact, not a substitute for assignment. | The current schema has no persisted workflow task/assignment resource, and 005I5 explicitly prohibits relabelling receiver/creator as assignment. 012EA already owns persisted task generation after workflow states exist. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` M04-FR-001/M04-FR-002; `docs/slices/012EA-workflow-task-engine-and-task-inbox-apis.md`; architecture review `2026-07-10_173305_architecture_review` | 012EA-workflow-task-engine-and-task-inbox-apis | High | Yes | 2026-07-10 | Epic 006 must not claim these IDs complete before 012EA creates one idempotent Deputy Manager – Finance appraisal task after application-number generation and backfills existing applications. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:59:| A-054 | Until source governance selects between application receipt and completeness confirmation for M04-FR-003, the current appraisal TAT anchor remains `LoanApplication.created_at`, the timestamp used by 006E as the available application-receipt proxy. | Functional M04-FR-003 says receipt / completeness confirmation, data-model §14.4 says application receipt + 2 days, and the current model has no completeness-confirmed timestamp. Choosing a different inferred timestamp would invent a rule. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` M04-FR-003; `docs/source/data-model.md` §14.4; `docs/slices/006E-appraisal-note-create-edit-submit.md`; architecture review `2026-07-10_173305_architecture_review` | 006E2 and future workflow-task/SLA governance | High | Yes | 2026-07-10 | Keep the anchor explicit in API/contracts and task due-date generation. If the owner confirms completeness confirmation, add a persisted confirmation timestamp and version the SLA rule without rewriting historical due dates. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:66:| A-061 | Explicitly revalidating a non-draft `legacy_unverified` appraisal must never make an old Credit Manager decision approve newly pinned prerequisite facts. A `review_pending` row may remain pending after revalidation because no terminal review exists; a `reviewed` row must return to draft, clear only its latest-review projection, preserve immutable review history, and require maker resubmission plus a fresh independent review. Rejected/submitted terminal rows remain quarantined until a separately governed repair exists. | ADR-0003 requires conservative provenance and fresh frozen facts, while migration 0005 can downgrade every state but the current repair is draft-only. Preserving a reviewed status after changing its evidence would silently transfer authority to facts the reviewer never saw; reopening is the conservative workflow default. The source does not define a legacy-remediation state machine, so the exception is explicit and reviewable. | `docs/adr/ADR-0003-freeze-appraisal-prerequisite-projections.md`; `docs/adr/ADR-0004-append-only-appraisal-review-decisions.md`; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §3/§24; `docs/source/data-model.md` §14.4/§34; architecture review `2026-07-10_213352_architecture_review` | 006E4-legacy-appraisal-remediation-and-history-backfill | High | Yes | 2026-07-10 | If governance defines another remediation flow, version the explicit action. Never silently relabel unproven facts, erase immutable review history, or let a pre-remediation review satisfy sanction gating. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:83:| A-080 | Approval-case read scope is persisted separately from `approvals.case.read`: immutable approvers keep assignment scope; the submitting Credit Manager keeps owner scope; Internal Auditor uses source `audit_readonly`; Company Secretary uses a narrowly named `legal_readonly` grant that permits routed package reads but never approval actions or assigned-queue membership. | Auth §§14.1/26.3 explicitly require Credit Manager, Company Secretary, and Auditor sanction-package reads, while §19.1 names audit/management scope but no exact Company Secretary object-scope code. A dedicated read-only grant is the conservative technical mechanism; treating the action permission or broad `management_readonly` as global case authority would recreate the 007C defect. | `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §§14.1, 19.1, 26.3, 27.1, 32.1, 37.3; architecture review `2026-07-13_131622_architecture_review` | 007C3-approval-case-source-read-scope-closure | High | Yes | 2026-07-13 | If governance names a different legal-read scope, migrate the grant vocabulary without widening action authority or rewriting immutable case history. |
