     6	## Parent Epic
     7	Epic 007: Sanction Approval Workflow and Registers
     8	Epic file: `docs/epics/007-sanction-approval-workflow.md`
     9	
    10	## Depends On
    11	- 007E
    12	
    13	## Runtime Capabilities
    14	
    15	none
    16	
    17	## Goal
    18	
    19	Close the independent-review defects in conflict replacement: preserve the exact number of
    20	distinct CFO/Director authorities, expose every replacement action in canonical case history, and
    21	keep unused committee candidates nondisclosed before list counts and pagination.
    22	
    23	## Source / Review References
    24	
    25	- `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §§16.2, 17.1-17.3, 19.1, 27.1, 32.1, and 37.3
    26	- `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §§25.3-25.8 and §44
    27	- `docs/source/data-model.md` §§15.3-15.5, §30, and §34
    28	- `docs/source/functional-spec.md` M05-FR-004..012
    29	- `docs/source/security-privacy.md` §§12.1-12.3
    30	- `docs/source/codebase-design.md` §§13.1-13.2, 26.1-26.3, 27.1, and 42.1-42.2
    31	- `docs/working/REVIEW_FINDINGS.md` entry for `2026-07-13_164911_architecture_review`
    32	
    33	## Concrete Requirements
    34	
    35	1. Resolve conflict replacements as distinct frozen authority slots. A user may occupy at most one
    36	   effective slot; excluding either Director on a CFO + two-Director route cannot reuse the other
    37	   Director twice. Authority is satisfiable only when the exact configured role counts are filled
    38	   by distinct non-conflicted frozen candidates. Otherwise enrichment/abstention atomically closes
    39	   the case as `blocked_by_conflict`, creates no sanction, and records the exact missing role.
    40	2. Keep `required_approvers_json` immutable as route provenance, but make the one canonical
    41	   collection/detail/action projection show the executable replacement mapping and every immutable
    42	   action. An approved case cannot display an excluded original Director as undecided while hiding
    43	   the alternate's approval. Document the response shape in `API_CONTRACTS.md`; collection, detail,
    44	   action, returned history, and later cycles must agree byte-for-byte on authority/action facts.
    45	3. Replace the read selector's over-broad committee-candidate index with an exact approval-owned
    46	   read projection: original required/history actors plus currently effective replacements, never
    47	   an unused committee alternate. Backfill existing rows deterministically. Ordinary list counts
    48	   and pagination must be exact in SQL; an unused second Director with `approvals.case.read` gets an
    49	   empty page with `total_count: 0` and direct `403 OBJECT_ACCESS_DENIED`.
    50	4. Apply COI-005 only after the base case object boundary. A conflicted actor retains limited
    51	   history read only if they were an original required actor, an effective replacement, or already
    52	   acted in that cycle. Merely appearing in the frozen committee candidate pool or in a declaration
    53	   cannot create read scope, queue membership, or action authority.
    54	5. Preserve complete related-party detection independently from committee assignment: active
    55	   borrower/Director-relative/Sanction-Committee-member declarations must set the immutable general-
    56	   meeting flag even when the related Director is not a current case approver. Conflict exclusions
    57	   still apply only to actual frozen authority candidates. Reject blank/whitespace declaration
    58	   reasons before enrichment can produce an incoherent routed case.
    59	6. Move coherence/read-index synchronization behind one explicit approval-owned projection updater
    60	   invoked by case creation, enrichment, actions/abstention, appraisal-driven refresh, and migration.
    61	   An ordinary model save must not hide cross-table workflow mutation or create a models-to-modules
    62	   ownership cycle. Tests must prove every production writer refreshes the projection atomically.
    63	
    64	## Test Cases
    65	
    66	- Public enrichment and final-action paths for CFO + two Directors with Director 1 excluded,
    67	  Director 2 excluded, both alternates unavailable, and self-abstention; assert distinct role/user
    68	  sets and exact no-sanction blocked ledgers.
    69	- One-Director replacement through collection, detail, approve response, final readback, and
    70	  returned history; the alternate decision/acted-at/replacement attribution is visible everywhere
    71	  while immutable route provenance is unchanged.
    72	- Unused committee alternate with read permission, with a declaration, and after grant removal:
    73	  ordinary/assigned counts remain zero and detail/action stay nondisclosing with zero writes.
    74	- General-meeting flag matrix for Director borrower, Director relative, committee-member borrower,
    75	  non-committee related Director, material interest only, and maker-checker only.
    76	- Each §17.1 class crosses public enrichment -> queue/detail -> approve/reject/return denial with the
    77	  exact §17.3 response and sole COI-006 audit exception; no manually injected exclusion may stand in
    78	  for the class under test.
    79	- Migration/backfill and query-count tests prove exact read projection, bounded SQL pagination, and
    80	  unchanged immutable case/action/audit/workflow/communication history.
    81	
    82	## Evidence Required
    83	
    84	Retain RED output for the three architecture-review probes, GREEN public authority/projection/scope
    85	matrices, migration proof, exact ledgers, focused API examples, and all configured gates.
    86	
    87	## Risk Level
    88	High
    89	
    90	## Acceptance Criteria
    91	
    92	- A configured Director count can never be satisfied by duplicate user identity.
